page.title: 01GENERAL DESCRIPTION
page.content: This D-Block includes parts of 5 parishes to the west of North Walsham. Felmingham,Suffield,Antingham, Swafield and North Walsham. The area around Antingham is fairly flat,open agricultural land.Cereals,sugar beet,peas,beans and potateos are the main crops grown on the medium light soil.The main woodland near here is Gunton Park.This is a Conservation Area which means you have to have special permission to cut trees or build or knock down buildings.The area between Antingham and North Walsham includes a small rather overgrown valley which was once part of the North Walsham and Dilham Canal.Bradfield Bridge is very big as it was probably built for barges_there is also a Barge Farm which seems to conect the area with canals although the canal is hardly visible now.
